    • Method Detail

      • addMenuParts

        public static void addMenuParts(org.bukkit.entity.Player player,
                                org.bukkit.inventory.Inventory menu,
                                int startIndex)
        Fills the given main menu with sub menu icons.
        Row 1, Slot 1: The quest menu + completed quest count display.
        Row 1, Slot 2: The achievement menu + achievement count display.
        Row 1, Slot 3: The pet menu + used pet slots display.
        Row 2, Slot 1: The currency menu + coin amount display.
        Row 2, Slot 2: The titles menu + unlocked title count display.
        Row 2, Slot 3: The bestiary menu + killed enemy count display.
        Parameters:
        player - The player that should view the inventory.
        menu - The main menu inventory.
        startIndex - The first slot of the inventory to fill.

      • check

        Checks if an event in this inventory was triggered by a player click.
        Parameters:
        player - The placer who clicked a menu item.
        clicked - The item that was clicled.
        Returns:
        If an event was triggered.
        See Also:
        QuestMenu.open(Player), AchievementsMenu.open(Player), BreedingMenu.open(Player, int), CurrencyMenu.open(Player), TitleMenu.open(Player), BestiaryMenu.open(Player)
